President Uhuru Kenyatta and Opposition leader Raila Odinga have appointed a team of 14 advisors to steer national dialogue on building bridges initiative. The 14 persons are; Dr. Adams Oloo, Agnes Kavindu, Senator Amos Wako, Ms. Florence Omose, Prof. Saeed Mwanguni, James Matundura, Major (rtd) John Seii, Bishop Lawi Imathiu,  Maison Leshomo, Senator Mohamed Yusuf Haji, Morompi Ole Ronkai, Bishop Peter Njenga, Makueni County Women rep Rose Moseo and Zacchaeus Okoth. ALSO READ:

